Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting possible renal impairment and poor glycemic control. Hemoglobin A1c is unexpectedly low, possibly due to analytical or clinical factors (e.g., anemia, hemoglobinopathy). Recommend further evaluation for renal dysfunction and diabetes, and correlation with clinical findings. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Prompt nephrology and endocrinology assessment advised.
